defaultIn relation to buses in England, this is left to the market to 
defaultdetermine, with local authorities having powers to support non commercial services or to support community transport where they contribute to solving local transport problems, including social isolation.  In relation to local rail services, the level of se
defaultrvice is determined by the Department for Transport which specifies the franchise requirement.  
defaultLocal authorities are able to support additional local train services but are frequently constrained from doing so by the reduction in rate support grant by cen
defaulttral government and the inadequate remit on the provision of local rail services described above.
